{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Fire Rabbit also known as 丁卯''' (hinotou, teika nou, teika nousagi, teibou) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 4th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingyin|ja|丙寅|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Wuchun|ja|戊辰|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Rabbit|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft|12=draft}}, forming a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Wood gives rise to Fire).

