It is the 4th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingyin|ja|丙寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bingyin|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Wuchun|ja|戊辰|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wuchun|qq=}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tei|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoto (丁)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Rabbit|ja|卯|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|2=ja|3=卯|4=fr|5=Lapin (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Konijn (astrologie)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|1=Rabbit (zodiac)|lt=Rabbit (卯)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rabbit|13=User:Immanuelle/Rabbit (zodiac)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Wood|ja|木|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood|qq=}}, forming a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutual Generation|qq=}}) (i.e. Wood gives rise to Fire).

